      <h2>About Money Kids <span class="badge">Version 1.0</span></h2>
      <p><strong>Creator:</strong> Jacob Nguyen</p>
      <p><strong>Short Description:</strong> Money Kids is an educational finance app that helps children and beginners learn about saving, spending, and earning money through interactive lessons, quizzes, and games.</p>
      <p class="meta">Platform: iOS (App Store)</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>Need help or want to share feedback? Email us and we’ll respond within 1–2 business days.</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:moneykidshelp@gmail.com">moneykidshelp@gmail.com</a></p>
      <p class="meta">Support hours: Mon–Fri, 9am–5pm ET</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>

      <h3>How do I reset my progress?</h3>
      <p>Open the app → Settings → Account → <em>Reset Progress</em>. You’ll be asked to confirm before clearing quizzes and streaks.</p>

      <h3>Do I need an account to use Money Kids?</h3>
      <p>No, you can use the app without an account. Creating one lets you save progress across devices.</p>

      <h3>Is Money Kids free?</h3>
      <p>Core lessons are free. Optional features or themes may require in-app purchases or subscriptions in the future.</p>

      <h3>How do I report a bug or suggest a feature?</h3>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:moneykidshelp@gmail.com">moneykidshelp@gmail.com</a> and include your device model, iOS version, and any screenshots if possible.</p>

      <h3>Is Money Kids safe for children?</h3>
      <p>Yes! We designed Money Kids with children’s privacy and safety in mind, following COPPA and FERPA guidelines.</p>

      <h3>Does Money Kids work with schools or classrooms?</h3>
      <p>Yes. When used in schools, we act as a “school official” under FERPA, processing student data only for educational purposes.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> October 28, 2025</p>

      <h3>Who We Are</h3>
      <p><strong>Money Kids</strong> is developed by Jacob Nguyen. You can contact us at <a href="mailto:moneykidshelp@gmail.com">moneykidshelp@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Data (optional):</strong> name, email, and settings if you create an account.</li>
        <li><strong>Progress Data:</strong> completed lessons, streaks, and scores.</li>
        <li><strong>Diagnostics:</strong> crash logs and device type (no personal data).</li>
        <li><strong>Support Messages:</strong> contents of emails you send to our help team.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How We Use Information</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>To improve and personalize your app experience.</li>
        <li>To save and sync learning progress across devices.</li>
        <li>To respond to support requests and provide updates.</li>
        <li>To maintain safety and comply with legal requirements.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Children’s Privacy (COPPA)</h3>
      <p>We comply with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not collect more data than necessary for use.</li>
        <li>Features needing personal data require verifiable parental consent.</li>
        <li>Parents can review or delete their child’s information anytime by emailing us.</li>
        <li>No ads or tracking targeted to children.</li>
        <li>Third-party service providers are bound by strict confidentiality.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>School & Student Data (FERPA)</h3>
      <p>When used in schools, Money Kids follows the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>We act as a “school official” with legitimate educational interest.</li>
        <li>We use student data only for educational purposes requested by the institution.</li>
        <li>We never sell or use student data for advertising.</li>
        <li>Schools may access, modify, or delete student data upon request.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data Sharing</h3>
      <p>We share limited data only with service providers necessary for app operation (e.g., hosting). We never sell user data.</p>

      <h3>Security</h3>
      <p>We use reasonable safeguards to protect your data. No system is completely secure, but we continually enhance protections.</p>

      <h3>Data Retention</h3>
      <p>We retain personal data only as long as necessary to operate the app. You may request deletion anytime at <a href="mailto:moneykidshelp@gmail.com">moneykidshelp@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h3>Your Rights</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the app without an account if you prefer.</li>
        <li>Request to view, correct, or delete your data.</li>
        <li>Parents and schools have additional rights under COPPA and FERPA.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>International Users</h3>
      <p>The app operates from the U.S.; data may be processed there under U.S. privacy laws.</p>

      <h3>Policy Updates</h3>
      <p>We may update this policy periodically. The effective date above will always reflect the latest version.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Legal & Policies</h2>
      <p>This page serves as both our Support and Privacy Policy. For any other questions, contact <a href="mailto:moneykidshelp@gmail.com">moneykidshelp@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </section>
